Name: Adam Kafia
Title: Software engineer | NestJS developer | Backend developer
About:
As a highly skilled backend developer and software engineer with over 700 hours of experience as a freelancer, I specialize in developing and maintaining scalable and reliable server-side systems using NodeJS, Express, NestJS, API, Rest API, MongoDB, Mongoose, MySQL, and PostgreSQL, with a strong focus on cloud technologies such as AWS and GCP. I am also experienced in using Tauri to build fast, secure, and scalable desktop applications.
I am looking to connect with like-minded professionals and explore new opportunities in the backend development field, with a focus on cloud technologies such as AWS and GCP, as well as building desktop applications with Tauri.
I have a track record of success in delivering high-quality, scalable solutions to complex problems as a freelancer on Upwork. In my previous roles, I have developed and maintained a range of server-side systems, including a serverless event-driven architecture for a real-time messaging platform and a secure authentication system using JSON Web Tokens. I have extensive experience working with CI/CD pipelines on both Bitbucket and GitHub, and am skilled in implementing automated testing and deployment processes to ensure the timely delivery of high-quality software. I am also familiar with Atlassian Jira and Confluence, and have experience using these tools to manage project workflows and collaborate with team members.
